<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p class="p">We analyze the atmospheric moisture budget to quantify the changes in the hydrological cycle. A detailed derivation and discussion of the possible errors can be found in Li and Ting (
 <xref rid="grl56839-bib-0027" ref-type="ref" class="xref">2017</xref>) and Seager and Henderson (
 <xref rid="grl56839-bib-0038" ref-type="ref" class="xref">2013</xref>). In steady state, the following balance can be expressed in pressure coordinates as 
 <disp-formula id="grl56839-disp-0001" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(1)</label>
  <math id="nlm-math-1" class="math">
   <mover accent="false" class="mover">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">P</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mo accent="true" class="mo">¯</mo>
   </mover>
   <mo class="mo">−</mo>
   <mover accent="false" class="mover">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">E</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mo accent="true" class="mo">¯</mo>
   </mover>
   <mo class="mo">=</mo>
   <mo class="mo">−</mo>
   <mfrac class="mfrac">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mn class="mn">1</mn>
    </mrow>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">g</mi>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">ρ</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">w</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mfrac>
   <mo class="mo">∇</mo>
   <mo class="mo">·</mo>
   <mover accent="false" class="mover">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <munderover class="munderover">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mo class="mo">∫</mo>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mn class="mn">0</mn>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">p</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">s</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </munderover>
     <mi mathvariant="bold" class="mi">u</mi>
     <mi class="mi">q</mi>
     <mspace width="2.56804pt" class="mspace"/>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">d</mi>
     <mi class="mi">p</mi>
    </mrow>
    <mo accent="true" class="mo">¯</mo>
   </mover>
   <mo class="mo">≈</mo>
   <mo class="mo">−</mo>
   <mfrac class="mfrac">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mn class="mn">1</mn>
    </mrow>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">g</mi>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">ρ</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">w</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mfrac>
   <mo class="mo">∇</mo>
   <mo class="mo">·</mo>
   <munderover class="munderover">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo class="mo">∑</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">k</mi>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mn class="mn">1</mn>
    </mrow>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">K</mi>
    </mrow>
   </munderover>
   <mover accent="false" class="mover">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi mathvariant="bold" class="mi">u</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">k</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">q</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">k</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
    <mo accent="true" class="mo">¯</mo>
   </mover>
   <mspace width="1em" class="mspace"/>
   <msub class="msub">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mover accent="false" class="mover">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">Δp</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo accent="true" class="mo">¯</mo>
     </mover>
    </mrow>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">k</mi>
    </mrow>
   </msub>
   <mo class="mo">,</mo>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic class="italic">P</italic> is precipitation, 
 <italic class="italic">E</italic> is evaporation, 
 <italic class="italic">g</italic> is gravitational acceleration, 
 <italic class="italic">ρ</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">w</italic>
 </sub> is the density of water, 
 <italic class="italic">p</italic> is pressure and 
 <italic class="italic">p</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">s</italic>
 </sub> surface pressure, 
 <bold class="bold">u</bold> is the horizontal wind vector, 
 <italic class="italic">q</italic> is specific humidity, 
 <italic class="italic">k</italic> is the vertical level with a total of 
 <italic class="italic">K</italic> (here 
 <italic class="italic">K</italic> = 10, from 1,000 hPa to 200 hPa), and Δ
 <italic class="italic">p</italic> is the pressure thickness. Overbars represent monthly mean values.
</p>
